text: Oak Cane Branch is a stream in the U.S. state of Georgia. It is a tributary to the Ogeechee River. Variant names were "O'Cain Creek", "O'Kane Branch", "Oak Cane Creek", "Ocain's Branch", and "Ocains Branch". The present name is a corruption of the last name of Daniel O'Cain, an 18th-century landholder. ==References== Category:Rivers of Georgia (U.S. state) Category:Bodies of water of Jenkins County, Georgia
